<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAIDERS; PRICE IS RIGHT FOR HIS PROTECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Raider practice field looked like a driving range early Wednesday morning. 
</P>
<P>
 Offensive linemen Steve Wisniewski, Kevin Gogan and Dan Turk were chipping 
golf balls, trying out the new clubs presented to them by quarterback Jeff 
Hostetler. 
</P>
<P>
 Hostetler gave each of his linemen a set of clubs and a golf bag as a reward 
for their season of protection. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was a great gesture on his part," lineman Greg Skrepenak said. "He's a 
great individual and he just showed it. We thank him and, hopefully, we'll show 
our thanks by giving him all the time (he needs to pass) on Saturday." 
</P>
<P>
 Asked how many of the linemen play golf, Hostetler said, "We'll find out." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Safety Eddie Anderson, who missed last Sunday's game because of a groin pull, 
did not practice Wednesday, but Coach Art Shell won't rule him out for 
Saturday. STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
