<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; FOCUSED MATER DEI ROUTS LOUISVILLE BALLARD, 70-49 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Just when it seemed Mater Dei was scratching to survive, the Monarchs go out 
and maul somebody. 
</P>
<P>
 They had just hung on Tuesday, but seemed determined not to let Louisville 
Ballard hang around Wednesday.A second-half blitz led to the Monarchs' 70-49 
victory at Las Vegas Durango High School, putting Mater Dei in today's Reebok 
Holiday Prep Classic semifinals this morning against Washington, D.C. Dunbar, a 
77-71 winner over Las Vegas Durango. The championship game is tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 "We came out focused tonight," said guard Clay McKnight, who scored 15 points. 
"We knew our defense would lead to some offense." 
</P>
<P>
 The Monarchs overwhelmed the Bruins (4-3) in the second half, outscoring them, 
35-18. Mater Dei led, 35-31, at halftime, then left Ballard gagging on fumes. 
</P>
<P>
 The key was a 13-0 run that gave Mater Dei a 52-33 lead with nine minutes 
left. Schea Cotton scored six of those points and Kevin Augustine four. 
</P>
<P>
 This was the same Augustine who was one for seven from the field Tuesday, one 
reason the Monarchs barely survived Federal Way (Wash.) Decatur, 49-48. 
Augustine, a sophomore point guard, scored 10 points against Ballard, making 
all four of his shots. 
</P>
<P>
 "I can do other things to help the team beside score," Augustine said. "But 
when I get my points, it seems to free up the other guys." 
</P>
<P>
 Guys like Cotton, for instance. He scored 24 points, making 10 of 14 shots. He 
made his last seven shots before fouling out with three minutes left. 
</P>
<P>
 "Tonight, that was what Schea Cotton is all about," Coach Gary McKnight said. 
"When he shoots like that, he's scary." CHRIS FOSTER 
</P>
</TEXT>
