<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; FIVE ANAHEIM WRESTLERS PIN OPPONENTS IN ROUT OF KATELLA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alexei Yanuaria was one of five Anaheim wrestlers who had pins in the 
Colonists' 47-18 victory over Katella in a nonleague match Wednesday at 
Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 Yanuaria, ranked second in the county at 130 pounds, had the fastest pin in 
1:16. Other Anaheim wrestlers to record pins were Richard Ramirez (119), Alex 
Coria (125), Danny Mejia (145) and Leonard Ruiz (160). Katella also had to 
forfeit four matches. 
</P>
<P>
 Katella's Hung Huynh defeated Jose Lopez, 5-4, in the 112-pound match. Lopez 
usually wrestles at 103 pounds, at which is ranked No. 1. Katella had another 
victory when third-ranked Eric Schirmacher (171) defeated fourth-ranked Robert 
Droughns, 6-2. Anaheim improved to 16-2. Katella is 6-6. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 9, Loara 0 -- The top-ranked Eagles scored four goals in the 
first 11 minutes. Chon Kantikovit, Seth George and Matt Blasdel each scored 
twice for Santa Margarita (9-0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna 5, Costa Mesa 3 -- Savanna's Julio Palacio broke a 2-2 halftime tie 
with three goals in the second half. Jose Albarran had eight saves for Savanna 
(4-2-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Claremont girls' soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 0, Temecula Valley 0 (3-1 in shootout) -- Christine Geske stopped 
Temecula Valley's third attempt in the shootout to preserve the consolation 
victory for Brea-Olinda (7-1-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In a second-round game, Christine Geske had seven saves for Brea-Olinda, which 
lost to Claremont, 1-0.  
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 2, Hacienda Heights Wilson 0 -- Amy Lemke and Jenny Ryan both scored 
unassisted goals for Fullerton in the fourth-round shutout. 
</P>
<P>
 In a third-round game, San Bernardino San Gorgono defeated Fullerton, 4-3. 
Fullerton (3-5-2) will play in the semifinal round at 9 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Simi Valley girls' soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 2, Thousand Oaks La Reina 0 -- For fourth-ranked Capistrano 
Valley (10-2), Jen Tomczik and Kelly Skeen each scored in the first half of the 
third-place game. 
</P>
