<TEXT>
<P>
 In the Catalina tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 71, Avalon 53 -- Brent Zakaryan and Eric Chenowith each scored 12 
points to lead Villa Park (6-2) in the championship final. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Chino Hills Ayala tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos Valley Christian 68, Liberty Christian 45 -- Bryan Avery scored 20 
points and Greg Rule had 14 rebounds for Liberty Christian (4-7) in the 
11th-place game. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Encinitas San Dieguito boys' basketball tournament semifinal game: 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 62, San Diego St. Augustine 56 -- Ninth-ranked Santa Margarita 
outscored St. Augustine, 35-28, in the second half. Allen Krist had 14 points 
and 10 rebounds and Brendan Mulligan had 11 points and 10 rebounds for the 
Eagles (9-0). 
</P>
<P>
 In the consolation round of the Sacramento Tracy Tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 68, Stockton McClatchy 66 -- Mike Ogas scored 24 points, Josh Lightman 
added 13 and Bradley Lisotto 10 to lead Edison (4-6). The Chargers will face 
Stockton Tracy in the consolation championship at 4:30 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague boys' basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress 64, Troy 55 -- Derek Mitchell scored 19 points to lead 10th-ranked 
Cypress (9-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Honolulu St. Louis 53, El Toro 33 -- Moody Michael, Mark Wulfemeyer and Travis 
Senik each scored six points for host El Toro (4-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 61, Aliso Niguel 38 -- Mike Pahl and Carlos Romero each scored 14 
points to lead Katella (10-0). Tim Bragasso's 11 points led Aliso Niguel (4-6). 
</P>
<P>
 La Habra 75, Valencia 58 -- Dan Ploog led four players in double figures for 
La Habra (5-5) with 25 points and seven rebounds. Kevin Jackley and James 
Rivera paced Valencia with 12 points each. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View 73, Marina 54 -- Dan McDonald had 21 points and nine rebounds and 
Ali Enriquez added 13 points and five assists to lead Ocean View (6-5). 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Ana 54, Santiago 51 -- Danny Rivero scored 13 points to lead Santa Ana 
(4-5). Santiago's Ralph Nelson was the game's leading scorer with 25 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna 49, Kennedy 44 -- David Draghinas scored 22 points to lead Savanna 
(8-3). Richie Bowen had 14 points for Kennedy (4-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Servite 48, Esperanza 46 -- David Downs scored eight of his 20 points in the 
fourth quarter as Servite (7-2) overcame a three-point deficit. Josh Greer had 
20 points to lead Esperanza (5-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 61, Magnolia 31 -- Fifth-ranked Sonora (8-2) jumped to a 32-13 
first-half lead. Chad Fister had 16 points and Craig Clark 12 to lead the 
Raiders. 
</P>
