<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; CLOSER NOT ENOUGH FOR NORTHRIDGE WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cal State Northridge women's basketball team is still looking for its 
first victory of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors dropped their eighth consecutive game, losing to Southwest Texas 
State, 64-45, on Wednesday night in a nonconference game at Matador Gym. 
</P>
<P>
 For Northridge, which has suffered defeats by as many as 47 and 44 points, at 
least it wasn't as lopsided. 
</P>
<P>
 Shannon Crouse scored 13 points for the Matadors, making five of 11 shots. 
Carrie Dormire had nine points and nine rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Marcie Atkins scored 14 points to for Southwest Texas State (4-3). Yolanda 
Wilkerson added 12 points and six rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 In other women's basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 85, Feather River 45 -- Kyetra Brown scored 27 points and had five 
steals to lead Canyons (11-2) in the first round of the Sacramento City 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Kerri Garland grabbed 20 rebounds to go with 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 84, El Camino 46 -- Julie Hardy scored 21 points and Amber Magner 
added 19 for Ventura (10-1) in a nonconference game at El Camino. Tori Anderson 
had 16 points and 10 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos 76, Moorpark 56 -- Every player in uniform for the Falcons (9-4) 
scored in the nonconference victory at home. Guard Tara Knesel scored 16 points 
on eight-for-11 shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Janette Oriza had 23 points and 12 rebounds for Moorpark (1-10), which had 
only seven players. Misty Goodnight had seven assists for the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark led, 32-29, at halftime, but the Falcons outscored the Raiders, 
47-24, in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark outrebounded Cerritos, 44-36. The Raiders shot 42% from the field, 
while Cerritos shot 41%. 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos made five of seven three-point shots, while Moorpark made only one of 
nine. BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth 86, Los Altos 64 -- Junior Eddie Miller scored 19 points and 
grabbed 16 rebounds for the Chancellors (7-1) in a semifinal game of the Bonita 
