<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; ANTEATERS WIN AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UC Irvine women's basketball team scored an 84-80 victory over winless 
North Texas Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Junior Allah-mi Basheer had 20 points, including 18 in the second half, and 
seven rebounds and Michelle Kahler added 15 points and seven rebounds to lead 
visiting UC Irvine (3-3). 
</P>
<P>
 The victory marked the first time the Anteaters, who beat Texas Christian 
Sunday, have won consecutive road games since 1988. It also marked the first 
time the Anteaters recorded back-to-back victories since 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 The 3-3 start is the best for the Anteaters since 1991, when they also started 
the season 3-3. 
</P>
<P>
 Jinelle Williams had 11 points and Tamera Thomas had 11 points, including 
three three-pointers, for the Anteaters, who shot 45.7% from the floor. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaquinta Deaton had a game-high 24 points and team-high six rebounds for North 
Texas (0-7). 
</P>
