<HEADLINE>
<P>
SADDLEBACK GIVES BRUMMEL VICTORY NO. 250 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Saddleback Coach Bill Brummel gained the 250th victory of his career when the 
Gauchos beat Grossmont, 75-58, in a nonconference men's basketball game 
Wednesday at Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 Brummel, in his 14th season, has a record of 250-157 and led the Gauchos to 
the Orange Empire Conference title (his third) in 1993 and a second-place 
finish last season.His 1987 team reached the final of the State tournament only 
to fall to Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Micah Kroger scored 18 points and Anthony Carter added 12 for the Gauchos 
(10-3). Each had five rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Frank Allen added 10 points and five assists. But the strongest performance 
came from Keith Gwyn, a freshman from Dallas. He had 11 points and 13 rebounds, 
starting in place of sophomore Eric Ambrozich, who sat out because of a sore 
leg. 
</P>
<P>
 Even without Ambrozich, who is 6 feet 7, Saddleback outrebounded Grossmont, 
51-37. Grossmont (6-8) was led by Damion Willis who had 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Lloyd Lake added 13 points, including nine of 10 free throws, for the 
Griffins. 
</P>
