BRIEFLY; HEALTH: $50,000 FOR HIV-POSITIVE WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A local AIDS health center has received $50,000 from the Elton John AIDS 
Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 The AIDS Healthcare Foundation, a nonprofit support service organization 
specializing in care for women who are HIV-positive, will use the money for its 
outpatient clinical services. 
</P>
<P>
 "This generous grant from the Elton John AIDS Foundation allows us to continue 
and expand our work of providing quality medical care to women," said Dr. 
Charles Farthing, medical director of the AIDS Healthcare Foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 The AIDS Healthcare Foundation's four Los Angeles County clinics offer free 
routine gynecological care and family planning, among other services. 
</P>
