COMMUNITY NEWS: CRENSHAW; BLACK HISTORY EXHIBIT SEEKS ART BY SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Works by artists age 65 and older are being sought for the "Artists' Salute to 
Black History Month," an annual black art exhibit that opens in February at the 
Baldwin Hills Crenshaw Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
 This year's theme is "Our Elders . . . Our Foundations." 
</P>
<P>
