<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WEST HOLLYWOOD; CITY'S GIFT TO SHOPPERS: FREE HOLIDAY PARKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There may be no free lunch, but the city is offering free parking over the 
Christmas holiday weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 West Hollywood Mayor Abbe Land has announced that the city will not charge for 
parking at more than 1,600 meters throughout the city. 
</P>
<P>
 "According to our business community, these are some of the busiest shopping 
days," Land said. "The free holiday parking program is a nice gesture to our 
residents and business owners." 
</P>
<P>
 The free meter parking, from Friday through Monday, will cost the city about 
$50,000 in revenue, but the upturn in the local economy has made the program 
possible, Land said. The meters usually cost 25 cents for each 20 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 The meters will be covered with festive red-and-white bags. Although no money 
is necessary in the meters, parking time limits will still be enforced, Land 
warned.  
</P>
<P>
 The City Council initiated the program to demonstrate its appreciation to 
tourists who frequent West Hollywood businesses during the holidays, Land said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
