<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; FLORIDA; ADOPTION BY PARENTS WITH HIV IS REVERSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A judge in St. Petersburg, Fla., decided to reverse the adoption of a 
3-year-old girl after discovering that her adoptive parents are infected with 
the AIDS virus. Circuit Judge Horace Andrews said he did not know the couple 
were infected when he granted the adoption earlier this year, since a law 
protects the confidentiality of people with AIDS.He said he would nullify the 
adoption next month on grounds of "fraud or mistake," unless the couple give up 
their paternal rights first. The ruling came at the request of the state 
Department of Health and Rehabilitative Services. Agency officials objected to 
placing the girl with terminally ill parents, although HRS employees had been 
aware of the couple's diagnosis but recommended the adoption anyway. 
</P>
