<TEXT>
<P>
 A Japanese court ordered a school Tuesday to pay compensation for working a 
teacher to death. 
</P>
<P>
 The Okayama District Court ordered the Shimbi Gakuen school to pay $123,000 to 
the family of Yoshinomi Tanaka, who died in 1986 at age 44 from a brain 
hemorrhage. 
