</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Yasser Arafat's supporters scored a victory with 76% of the vote in a student 
election at Al Azhar University in the PLO-ruled Gaza Strip. 
</P>
<P>
 The outcome of Tuesday's election at Al Azhar University contrasted with 
balloting Dec. 5 at the neighboring Islamic University, where Islamic activists 
won all 12 student council seats with 98% of the vote. Arafat's Fatah faction, 
apparently fearing defeat, boycotted that election. 
</P>
