<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALFRED W. DITOLLA; ENTERTAINMENT UNION LEADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Alfred W. DiTolla, entertainment union executive and president of the 
International Alliance of Theatrical Stage Employees for the last eight years. 
DiTolla resigned Friday, citing ill health after brain surgery last 
summer.During his tenure, the union increased from 60,000 members to 76,000. 
DiTolla attended Fordham University and the New York Law School, then began his 
career as a charter member of the Broadcasting Studio Employees Local 782. He 
merged it with Radio and Television Sound Effects employees and served as the 
combined group's business representative. DiTolla became a working member of 
the stagehand alliance in New York in 1955. He advanced to international 
representative in 1974, assistant to the president in 1978 and president in 
1986. The Theatrical Mutual Assn. honored him as its Entertainment Man of the 
Year in 1986, and in 1993 Variety named him Father of the Year for his work for 
Children's Charity. On Tuesday in New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
