<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SANTA ANA; VOLUNTEERS NEEDED FOR HOLIDAY DINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Christmas Eve dinner for needy children and their families is being 
organized by the Santa Ana Unified School District and the Delhi Community 
Center. Volunteers and donations are needed for this fourth annual event. 
</P>
<P>
 "At least 2,000 Santa Ana Unified School District students are homeless," said 
Don Champlin, the district's interim superintendent. "These children have no 
holiday tree, presents or warm meal. We're trying to make the holiday season a 
little better for them." 
</P>
<P>
 A turkey dinner will be served from 11 a.m. to 2 p.m. Saturday at Festival 
Hall, 220 E. 3rd St. in Santa Ana. Children will receive presents from Toys for 
Tots. Toy donations may be dropped off at the elementary division of the school 
district office, 1405 French St. in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 558-5523. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
