<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; MARINERS LIBRARY PLANS ACTIVITIES FOR 
CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Just as the holidays are winding down, local children will have a new 
adventure to look forward to with the start of "Mariners Madness" at the 
Mariners Branch Library. 
</P>
<P>
 The free, structured activities for children in grades one through six will 
begin Jan. 3 under the direction of library and city recreation staff.The 
activities will last through the year. 
</P>
<P>
 They include: 
</P>
<P>
 * SuperStars, from 2 to 5 p.m. Mondays. The weekly event will feature games 
with a competitive spirit, including carom tournaments, relay races and 
obstacle course contests. 
</P>
<P>
 * Stories for Big Kids, at 3 p.m. Tuesdays. Librarian Jana Pratt will share 
local tales as well as those from around the world. 
</P>
<P>
 * Creative Encounters, from 2:30 to 4 p.m. Wednesdays. Pratt and guest artists 
will help children learn to express themselves through multimedia art 
activities. Preregistration is required for participation in the program. 
</P>
<P>
 * Friday Flix, at 3:15 p.m. Fridays, will feature screenings of popular videos 
in the Vincent Jorgensen Community Center next to the library. 
</P>
<P>
 The new activities will be paired with a free and supervised play in Mariners 
Park. Parents of children participating in the program must fill out emergency 
notification cards. 
</P>
<P>
 To register for the art program or for more information, call Frank Eastman at 
(714) 644-3145; for information only, call the Recreation Department at (714) 
644-3151. HOLLY J. WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
