<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; 25-CENT 
BUS, RAIL FARES SET FOR 2 HOLIDAY EVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Metropolitan Transportation Authority board decided Wednesday to offer a 
25-cent fare on Christmas Eve and New Year's Eve to discourage people from 
driving drunk. 
</P>
<P>
 The lowered fare, available on bus and rail lines, will be offered from 9 p.m. 
to 5 a.m. on both holidays. 
</P>
<P>
 "These two nights historically experience a high incidence of traffic 
accidents, due largely to an increase in intoxicated drivers on area roads and 
freeways," said Franklin White, MTA's chief executive officer. "We invite those 
wishing to spend the evenings with relatives or friends to let MTA bus and 
train operators bring them home safely," White said. 
</P>
