<P>
RANCHO SANTIAGO PLANS DATES FOR SIGN-UPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Enrollment for the 1995 spring semester at Rancho Santiago Community College 
will take place from Jan. 3 to 13 at the Orange and Santa Ana campuses, a 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Students should apply now for an early appointment.For specific hours of 
admission and registration at each site, students can call the Santa Ana campus 
at (714) 564-6000 or the Orange campus at (714) 564-4000. 
</P>
<P>
 Instruction begins Jan. 17, district spokesman Dale Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The spring schedule of classes includes a complete list of credit courses and 
information on financial aid, registration procedures and other student 
services. The schedules are available at the bookstores of both campuses, he 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santa Ana campus is at 17th and Bristol streets. The Orange campus is at 
8045 E. Chapman Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Continuing education classes take place at the Centennial Education Center, 
2900 W. Edinger Ave., in Santa Ana, and at the Orange Adult Learning Center, 
541 N. Lemon St. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on admission and registration, call the Centennial campus 
at (714) 564-5000 or the Orange center at (714) 564-5300.JON NALICK 
</P>
