<P>
CLAYTON, WREN SELECT SCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Clayton of Orange Coast and Jim Wren of Fullerton, All-Mission Conference 
players, signed with four-year colleges Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Clayton, a running back from Trabuco Hills High, is going to Texas. Wren, a 
punter from Esperanza High, will attend USC. 
</P>
<P>
 Clayton set the OCC career rushing mark with 2,507 yards in 21 games. He 
gained 1,442 yards and was a J.C. Grid-Wire All-American as a freshman. He had 
1,065 yards last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Wren averaged 42.3 yards a kick this season and was an honorable-mention 
All-American selection by the J.C. Grid-Wire. STEVE KRESAL 
