<HEADLINE>
<P>
AROUND THE VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 DUARTE: Three members of the City Council, who last month made up the council 
majority that enacted a 3% utility tax, have received notices they are the 
targets of a recall drive. Mayor James D. Kirchner, Councilman John R. Fasana 
and Councilman Philip R. Reyes were served with the notices Tuesday night by 
Duarte Taxpayer CARES (Citizens Against Rampant Expenditure Syndrome) as 
required by state law.Lino Paras, the group's spokesman, said the recall drive 
would stop only if the council puts the tax to a public vote. The group must 
gather the signatures of 2,156 registered voters who are city residents to put 
the recall on the ballot. 
</P>
<P>
 SOUTH PASADENA: The city has filed a notice with the court that it will appeal 
a reduced award of $500,000 to former Mayor Lee D. Prentiss. The City Council 
made the decision Dec. 7 in closed session. After a Pasadena Superior Court 
Judge slashed the $1.2-million jury award to $500,000 last month, Prentiss 
chose to accept it. 
</P>
