<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPENDED FIRE CHIEF FILES CLAIM AGAINST CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Suspended Pasadena Fire Chief Kaya Pekerol has filed a legal claim seeking 
unspecified damages against the city, alleging that City Manager Philip Hawkey 
and other officials conspired to discredit his job performance. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawkey, who has denied any wrongdoing toward Pekerol, has declined to divulge 
why Pekerol was suspended last month, saying it is a confidential personnel 
matter. 
</P>
<P>
 But in his Dec. 7 claim against the city, Pekerol said Hawkey told him he was 
being suspended with pay because he went to the City Council seeking a raise 
that Hawkey wouldn't give him. Pekerol is supposed to report directly to 
Hawkey. 
</P>
<P>
 Filing a claim against a government entity is usually considered a prelude to 
a lawsuit. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawkey and Pekerol attended a hearing on the suspension Tuesday, but no action 
was taken, a city spokeswoman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
