<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: FULLERTON; CITY ATTORNEY WILL RETIRE AT YEAR'S END 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Atty. R.K. Fox said Wednesday he will retire Dec. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 In October, Fox told city employees and the City Council that he has lung 
cancer and would be undergoing chemotherapy and radiation treatments over the 
next few months. 
</P>
<P>
 At the time, he wrote a memo saying he planned to continue working until he 
retired on an unspecified date. 
</P>
<P>
 Fox has not been attending City Council meetings and has spent only a few days 
at work since he announced his illness. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, Robert Bower of the Ruttan & Tucker law firm has been taking Fox's 
place. 
</P>
<P>
 Fox said his illness, which has affected his hearing, is not the reason he is 
retiring. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's just time to go," Fox, 60, said in a telephone interview from his home. 
"We've got a new City Council and they're entitled to choose their own city 
attorney."  
</P>
<P>
 The City Council has been meeting in closed sessions to discuss whether it 
should hire a permanent replacement for Fox or to contract the job. MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
