the shooting, Detective Rick Swanston said.Swanston said Pina ran away after 
Bernardo Martinez, 22, was shot once in the head. 
</P>
<P>
 Martinez and another friend went to visit Pina at his home in the 7300 block 
of Milwood Avenue about 10:15 p.m. Tuesday, Swanston said. "They're sitting 
there on the couch when Jaime Pina brings out his new gun," Swanston said. 
"When showing it to (Martinez), a round discharges" and hits Martinez in the 
head. 
</P>
