 Green Bay at Tampa Bay, 10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 New England at Chicago, 10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Seattle at Cleveland, 10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Kansas City at Raiders, 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Pittsburgh at San Diego, 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 SUNDAY 
</P>
<P>
 Detroit at Miami, 5 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 MONDAY 
</P>
<P>
 San Francisco at Minnesota, 6 p.m. POSSIBILITIES 
</P>
<P>
 AFC TEAMS 
</P>
<P>
 PITTSBURGH--Has clinched the Central title, a first-round bye and home-field 
advantage throughout the AFC playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN DIEGO--Has clinched the West title. Can clinch a first-round bye with a 
victory or tie with Pittsburgh or a Miami loss or tie with Detroit and a New 
England loss or tie at Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
 CLEVELAND--Has clinched a playoff berth. Will play host to a wild-card game 
with a victory or tie with Seattle or a Raider loss or tie with Kansas City. 
</P>
<P>
 MIAMI--Has clinched a playoff berth. Can clinch the East title with a victory 
over Detroit or a New England loss at Chicago. Can clinch a first-round bye 
with a victory over Detroit and a San Diego loss to Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
 RAIDERS--Can clinch a playoff berth with a victory or tie with Kansas City or 
a New England loss at Chicago. Can play host to a wild-card game with a victory 
over Kansas City and a Cleveland loss to Seattle. 
</P>
<P>
 NEW ENGLAND--Can clinch a playoff berth with a victory or tie at Chicago or a 
Kansas City loss at Raiders. Can clinch the East title with a victory at 
Chicago and a Miami loss or tie to Detroit. Can clinch a first-round bye with a 
victory at Chicago and a Miami loss or tie to Detroit and a San Diego loss to 
Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
 KANSAS CITY--Can clinch a playoff berth with a victory over the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
 NFC TEAMS 
</P>
<P>
 SAN FRANCISCO--Has clinched the West title, a first-round bye and home-field 
advantage throughout the NFC playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 DALLAS--Has clinched the division title and first-round bye. 
</P>
<P>
 MINNESOTA--Can clinch a playoff berth with either a tie with San Francisco or 
a Chicago loss to New England or a Detroit loss at Miami or a Green Bay loss or 
tie at Tampa Bay or an Arizona loss or tie at Atlanta or a New York Giant 
victory over Dallas. Can clinch the Central title with a victory over San 
Francisco. Can also clinch NFC Central title with losses by Detroit and Chicago 
and a Green Bay loss or tie at Tampa Bay. 
</P>
<P>
 DETROIT--Can clinch a playoff berth with a victory at Miami. Can also clinch a 
playoff berth with a tie with Miami and a Chicago loss to New England or a 
Green Bay loss or tie at Tampa Bay or a Minnesota victory or tie with San 
Francisco or a New York Giant victory over Dallas or an Arizona loss or tie at 
Atlanta. Can clinch the Central title with a victory at Miami and a Minnesota 
loss to San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
 CHICAGO--Can clinch a playoff berth with a victory over New England. Can also 
clinch a playoff berth with a tie with New England and a Green Bay loss or tie 
at Tampa Bay or a Minnesota victory or tie with San Francisco or a New York 
Giant victory over Dallas or an Arizona loss or tie at Atlanta. Can clinch NFC 
Central title with a victory over New England and if Minnesota and Detroit 
lose. 
</P>
<P>
 GREEN BAY--Can clinch a playoff berth with a victory at Tampa Bay or if 
Arizona and New York Giants lose. Can clinch the NFC Central title with a 
victory at Tampa Bay and if Minnesota, Detroit and Chicago all lose. 
</P>
<P>
 NEW YORK GIANTS--Can clinch a playoff berth with a victory over Dallas and a 
Green Bay loss or tie at Tampa Bay. 
</P>
<P>
 ARIZONA--Can clinch a playoff berth with a victory at Atlanta, a New York 
Giant loss or tie against Dallas and a Green Bay loss or tie at Tampa Bay. Can 
also clinch playoff berth with victory at Atlanta, a Minnesota loss to San 
Francisco and a victory by either Detroit, Chicago or Green Bay. PLAYOFF 
SCHEDULE 
</P>
