<HEADLINE>
<P>
MUSTAFA TO ATTEND ARIZONA STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Isaiah Mustafa, an all-state receiver at Moorpark College, said Wednesday that 
he has signed a letter of intent to play at Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
 "The campus was everything I hoped for," Mustafa said."As soon as I took the 
(recruiting) trip my mind was made up." 
</P>
<P>
 Mustafa, 6 feet 3, 210 pounds, set a Raider single-season record this year 
with 66 receptions and 1,086 yards. He scored 10 touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Mustafa, a former Santa Clara High basketball standout and two-time state 
decathlon runner-up at Moorpark, had not played football for several years 
before joining the Raiders in 1993. He was a starting free safety but was 
converted to receiver later that season. 
</P>
<P>
 Mustafa said that two factors played heavily in his decision to sign with the 
Sun Devils. 
</P>
<P>
 "I like their quarterback (Jake Plummer) and my sister lives in Tempe, so I'll 
be close to family," Mustafa said. FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
