<P>
BY DESIGN; DON'T BE A STUFFED SHIRT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA DENDEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here's an alternative to the stuffy traditional pleated white tuxedo shirt for 
the adventurous, stylish man of the '90s. 
</P>
<P>
 Inspired by the textiles from all over the world, New York designers Pinky 
Wolman and Thomas Oatman have created the cross-cultural tuxedo shirt. The one 
pictured is made of Swiss cotton with a tile batik bib from the Dutch East 
Indies. It sells from $220 at Maxfield in West Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 The designers also use Swiss cotton piques in unexpected formal co9lors, such 
as navy, and cotton ikats from Southeast Asia. JOANNA DENDEL 
</P>
