<TEXT>
<P>
 Ford Expects to Build Plant in Vietnam: The auto maker said it will build the 
assembly plant near Hanoi.It said it plans to apply for a license from the 
government early next year and begin construction as soon as the license is 
approved, said Wayne Booker, Ford's executive vice president for international 
operations. Ford Motor Co. and Song Cong Diesel Factory are completing a 
feasibility study for a joint venture to manufacture a complete line of cars 
and trucks for the Vietnamese market, Booker said. At first, the plant would 
