<P>
 More Good Economic Health Predicted for Wealthiest Nations: The Organization 
for Economic Cooperation and Development said in its latest semiannual Economic 
Outlook report that its 25 member nations can look forward to continued 
economic health in the next two years. In an unusually upbeat report, the 
Paris-based think tank said that as unemployment falls from recent record highs 
and inflation remains under control, the growth rate for member countries 
should quicken to 3% in 1995 from 2.8% this year and that growth should 
continue almost unabated into 1996. 
