<P>
 Bond fund -- While Orange County treasurer's office records show clearly that 
the office managed two funds, bankruptcy attorney Bruce Bennett said, external 
records, such as those of the banks that held many of the county's securities 
in trust, do not indicate any separation of funds. One fund was highly 
leveraged, the other invested in safer investments earning less interest. An 
article in Wednesday's paper mistakenly left the impression that Bennett said 
there was no documentation at all of two funds. 
</P>
